<h4>How to Use Our Applications &ndash; <strong>Single Bank Profile</strong></h4>
<p>1. From the <strong>BankAnalytics Dashboard</strong> click <strong>Single Bank Profile</strong>. This report allows you to view a rolling 5 Years or 5 Quarters of data for a specific Bank for 31 key data points.</p>
<p>2. Your Bank/Default Bank information will automatically populate the data fields and charts.There is a Quarter-to-Date (<strong>QTD</strong>) and Year-to-Date (<strong>YTD</strong>) tab (upper-right side of the page) that can be selected to change the data view.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">a. <strong>QTD</strong> shows a rolling 5 quarters of data.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">b. <strong>YTD</strong> shows a rolling 5 years of data, with current year being in one of 4 different states, YYYYQ1, YYYYQ2, YYYYQ3 or FY (Depending on the most recent data submitted to the FFIEC).</p>
<p>3. Data points for 5 period analysis include, <strong>Balance Sheet</strong>, <strong>Income Statement</strong>, <strong>Earnings and Performance</strong>, <strong>Asset Quality</strong>, <strong>Capital Ratios</strong>, and <strong>Liquidity</strong>.</p>
<p>4. Charted data with 5 period analysis include, <strong>Asset Growth Rate, Loans &amp; Leases Growth Rate, Deposit Growth Rate, Bank Equity Capital Growth Rate, Loan Composition, and Deposit Composition</strong>.</p>
<p>5. To Print the web page, click the <strong>Download&nbsp;PDF or Download Excel</strong> icon on the upper-right side of the page.</p>
<p>6. To View the Bank&rsquo;s website, click the <strong>Web Site</strong> hyperlink on the upper-left side of the page.</p>
<p>7. To change the bank being viewed, select a bank from the <strong>Select from Favorite Banks</strong> dropdown.</p>
<p>8. To use another bank as your "Defualt" bank in other apps, select the <strong>"Make Default"</strong> button in the top-right side of the page.</p>

